//A data analytics company is processing user activity numbers stored in an integer array.For every dataset, they need to identify two important metrics:
1.The Second Smallest activity value
2.The Second Largest activity value
These values help the company analyze the dataset by ignoring extreme outliers (minimum and maximum).
You are assigned to write a Java program to compute these two values.Given an integer array arr[], find:Second,Largest element
_*Note:*_
A. Consider only distinct values.
B. If second smallest OR second largest does not exist, print:"Second smallest and second largest do not exist"
C. Solve in O(n) time 
D. Assume array may contain duplicates.
*Test Case 01 :*
Input : arr = {12, 5, 7, 25, 18, 7, 12}
Output : 	
Second Smallest : 7
Second Largest  : 18
*Test Case 02 :*
Input : arr = {40, 40, 40, 40}
Output : Second smallest and second largest do not exist
*Test Case 03 :*
Input : arr = {9}
Output : Second smallest and second largest do not exist

import java.util.Scanner;

public class SecondSmallestLargest {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        // Input array size
        System.out.print("Enter array size: ");
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        // If array size is less than 2
        if (n < 2) {
            System.out.println("Second smallest and second largest do not exist");
            return;
        }

        int[] arr = new int[n];

        // Input array elements
        System.out.println("Enter array elements:");
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            arr[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        int smallest = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int secondSmallest = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int largest = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        int secondLargest = Integer.MIN_VALUE;

        for (int num : arr) {

            // Find smallest and second smallest
            if (num < smallest) {
                secondSmallest = smallest;
                smallest = num;
            } else if (num > smallest && num < secondSmallest) {
                secondSmallest = num;
            }

            // Find largest and second largest
            if (num > largest) {
                secondLargest = largest;
                largest = num;
            } else if (num < largest && num > secondLargest) {
                secondLargest = num;
            }
        }

        // Check if valid second smallest and largest exist
        if (secondSmallest == Integer.MAX_VALUE || secondLargest == Integer.MIN_VALUE) {
            System.out.println("Second smallest and second largest do not exist");
        } else {
            System.out.println("Second Smallest : " + secondSmallest);
            System.out.println("Second Largest  : " + secondLargest);
        }
    }
}
